FlavorText:
MESSAGE 70-DENI-XXXX

Winchester, we've secured the objective. We attached ourselves to 1st Flotilla and deployed via Halberd dropships to the station. Pathfinders were right, this is clearly of Venuman design but Fleet Intelligence couldn't put a date to the age of it, Meadows is adamant it's ancient. Strangely enough, it doesn't match the known designs in the databases and there's tech here that doesn't correlate to historical records, so in other words, we're looking at a possible blacksite here.

We did a run-through of the station, all hush-hush, and it turned out the entire station was drained of atmosphere and all the entry points were open to the vacuum, no bodies. We did come across a secure storage facility locked up behind a slew of automated defenses. We couldn't stick around long because Avery started to complain of headaches and hallucinations- Med-Techs said he was going on about some red guy in small spaces, I don't know- but we were able to get out with some devices we found in there, might be some psionic warfare weapon, don't really want to find out. I've sent you a sample, it's up to you what you want to do with them from here.

Locke
